Charisma Academy, an independent school in Rustenburg in the North West, says it’s doing all it can to stay afloat. Courtesy #DStv403 RUSTENBURG - Private schools are struggling to keep going in the lockdown. They were impacted by the initial school closure, and now many parents are unable to pay school fees. READ: Government gazettes new school calendar Their dire financial situation means at some schools, teachers can’t be paid or can’t be kept on. Charisma Academy, an independent school in Rustenburg in the North West, says it’s doing all it can to stay afloat. - Coronavirus Hotline Number: 0800 029 999 from 8 am to 4 pm, Monday to Friday. Help protect your loved ones by sharing this official South African government COVID-19 service with your family, friends and community. Send HI to 0600 123 456 on WhatsApp. The NICD has another Clinician Hotline to improve #COVID19 communication and support for healthcare providers. The Clinician Hotline is 0800 11 1131, operating 24 hrs. The Public Hotline is 0800 029 999 also operating 24hrs.